# ECC rules vendoring is RETIRED (2026-07-02). Nothing auto-loads
# ~/.claude/rules; the full upstream rules tree ships inside the ECC
# marketplace clone (~/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/ecc/rules/) wherever the
# plugin is installed, so the local copies bought sync code and churn for
# nothing. Machines that vendored before retirement may still have inert
# language dirs (common/ cpp/ python/ rust/ typescript/ web/) here -- this
# ignore keeps those leftovers from ever being committed.
#
# Only our OWN custom rules are version-controlled. Put them under
# claude/rules/personal/ and they are tracked by the whitelist below.
/*
!/.gitignore
!/personal/
